data.title: Fantastic Brunch
data.text: There's a lot to like about this little spot in downtown Round Rock. The location has character, being in an historic building. They have a nice little outdoor patio. The food is great, and the staff are friendly. Personally, I think their weekend brunch is the real standout here though. They offer a broad range of options from pancakes to migas to skillets and breakfast burgers. All options are really tasty. It's a bit small and they could use a few more beer taps for my tastes, but I always enjoy my visits.

data.title: Great sports bar
data.text: Had early afternoon meal and watched a euro 2016 match on one of the many screens that were available.  Food was good and plentiful for the price.  Staff very pleasant and accommodating ( rearranging the screens to put the match on a screen directly in front of us).

data.title: Good place to visit.
data.text: Recommended to me by a local it was well worth the visit. Fun atmosphere, good food. I would recommend it.

data.title: Good experience
data.text:
A new traveling job has me on the road a lot.  My goal is to find good quality food and friendly, relaxed atmosphere in non-chain restaurants as I go - places I can come back to next time in town.

The Rock met all these criteria in spades.  

I sat at the bar in the back room - Jeremy, working the bar, introduced himself, asked my name and shook my hand. His friendliness was nice and made me feel welcome (sometimes you don't get that as a stranger walking in to a local joint).

I get a little wary of over-talkative fake waiters - but he was genuine and it was totally comfortable and an appropriate amount of conversation and service.  The Italian sub (served warm) was tasty and the side of macaroni and cheese was excellent.

The Rock is now on my list.

data.title: Great bar, delicious food, local vibe
data.text: I love the back room at The Rock.  The friendly crowd and an excellent bartender lend to an enjoyable atmosphere.  Dinner specials every week day and lots of variety, so if you are hungry for salad, a sandwich or a big meal, there is something to suit on the menu.  Kudos for perfectly chilled white wines.  Plenty of parking in the free public lot behind the building.

data.title: My new downtown favorite in Round Rock!
data.text: We have had very consistent experiences here. We came a couple weeks ago and had drinks and their Friday night fajita special. The fajitas were really good.  They have a nice selection of draft beers (not as many as some places) but the service here is really good. We are always able to get someone to take our order and the beer is always poured just right and served at the right temperature.  My husband had a dirty martini and said it was one of the best he's had.  I highly recommend this place if you haven't been yet.

data.title: The Rock Sports Bar
data.text: Downtown Round Rock bar and grill.  Better than average bar food.  Great appetizers and a Sunday brunch!  2 full bars, lots of TV's and they carry my favorite brand of Chardonnay at a fantastic price!  The owners are sociable and seem to always be happy to see us when we go in.  It also always seems to be happily busy - in a good way. All the best to them!  I would recommend checking this place out.

data.title: Great Menu for a Sports Bar!
data.text: The menu was much better than I expected for a sports bar, and the food was great.  The atmosphere was good, and the service was excellent.  I have had friends tell me they also had great food and a good experience.  It can get a little noisy when crowded - which is what I would expect from a sports bar anyway.  New place in Round Rock - definitely a good addition to downtown.

data.title: Great comfort food at a great price!
data.text: Ate with the family, Chicken Fried Chicken was awesome. Hugh plate of chili fritos pie, definitely coming back!
